Thank you so much for drawing attention to this. That girl with the giant fish (5:30) has done it a lot to a wide variety of sea animals and it's frustrating that we can't get it taken down because it is, essentially, animal cruelty. She isn't educating anyone about it, she is torturing the animal before she kills it to eat it. If you want to eat fresh seafood, go right ahead. But don't hold it where it can't breathe for minutes while you try and get a laugh out of your audience before killing it. They've used "education" as a way to get around the animal cruelty that people have tried to flag her for and it's god damn bullshit!

Imagine instead of eating sea animals that can't make any noise, that girl (Ssoyoung) ate land animals that can yelp and whine, then she would be in trouble. She also chooses the animals that have 100% capability of feeling pain and suffering, it's not like "they're just fish they can't feel anything", I'm not a vegan who begs others to stop eating meat, I eat meat too but there is a correct way to kill an animal without putting it through such torment. This is absolutely not ok and the fact that youtube doesn't care is truly disappointing.
